The paper proposes a novel autoencoder architecture that improves novelty detection by promoting the learning of semantically meaningful features through adversarial robustness. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning, computer vision, and security. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely categories given the focus on improving autoencoder performance. Additionally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories given the use of adversarial robustness to improve feature learning.
